<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="267" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[130,777,1459,2028]" box="[132,222,1459,1485]" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[130,777,1459,2028]" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">
As in previous studies from 
<collectingCountry box="[433,505,1491,1517]" name="Ghana" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">Ghana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[559,614,1491,1517]" name="Togo" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">Togo</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="DE VREE F. &amp; DE ROO A. &amp; VERHEYEN W. N." pageId="16" pageNumber="267" pagination="200 - 207" refId="ref18033" refString="DE VREE F., DE ROO A. &amp; VERHEYEN W. N. 1969. - Contribution a l'etude des chiropteres de la Republique du Togo. Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines 83: 200 - 207." type="journal article" year="1969">
De Vree 
<emphasis box="[724,775,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">et al.</emphasis>
1969
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="DE VREE F. &amp; VAN DER STRAETEN E." box="[200,256,1523,1549]" pageId="16" pageNumber="267" pagination="159 - 164" refId="ref17980" refString="DE VREE F. &amp; VAN DER STRAETEN E. 1971. - Contribution a l'etude des chiropteres de la Republique duTogo. 3. Liste preliminaire des Chiropteres recoltes par la troisieme Mission zoologique belge au Togo. R evue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines 83: 159 - 164." type="journal article" year="1971">1971</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="DECHER J." box="[268,419,1523,1549]" pageId="16" pageNumber="267" pagination="129 - 142" refId="ref17648" refString="DECHER J. 1997 a. - Bat community patterns on the Accra Plains of Ghana, West Africa. Zeitschrift fur Saugetierkunde 62: 129 - 142." type="journal article" year="1997">Decher 1997a</bibRefCitation>
), with 23 individuals caught, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1868" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Micropteropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">Micropteropus pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was the most common small fruit bat in our survey, perhaps outnumbered locally only by large colonies of the high-flying 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kerr, 1792)" baseAuthorityName="Kerr" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[323,628,1618,1644]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Eidolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="helvum">
<emphasis box="[323,485,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">Eidolon helvum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="KERR R." box="[498,620,1618,1644]" pageId="16" pageNumber="267" refId="ref20152" refString="KERR R. 1792. - The animal kingdom, or zoological system, of the celebratrd Sir Charles Linnaeus; class I: Mammalia. J. Murray &amp; R. Faulder, London, 644 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 57940" type="book" year="1792">Kerr, 1792</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. It is a typical species of the rainforest-savannah mosaic characteristic for much of the 
<collectingRegion box="[272,416,1682,1708]" country="Ghana" name="Volta" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">Volta Region</collectingRegion>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[456,528,1682,1708]" name="Ghana" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">Ghana</collectingCountry>
east of the 
<collectingRegion box="[650,707,1682,1708]" country="Ghana" name="Volta" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">Volta</collectingRegion>
River, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[132,245,1714,1740]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Micropteropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[132,245,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">M. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously captured at Akwamufe, Amedzofe, Kalakpa Game Production Reserve, Leklebi Agbesia and Odomi Jongo (
<bibRefCitation author="BERGMANS W." box="[297,465,1778,1804]" pageId="16" pageNumber="267" pagination="89 - 153" refId="ref16941" refString="BERGMANS W. 1989. - Taxonomy and biogeography of African fruit bats (Mammalia, Megachiroptera). 2. The genera Micropterus Matschie, 1899, Epomops Gray, 1870, Hypsignathus H. Allen, 1861, Nanonycteris Matschie, 1899, and Plerotes Andersen, 1910. Beaufortia 39: 89 - 153." type="journal article" year="1989">Bergmans 1989</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[515,587,1778,1804]" name="Ghana" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">Ghana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[637,695,1778,1804]" name="Togo" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">Togo</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1868" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Micropteropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">M. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares a similar distribution pattern with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ogilby" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gambianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">Epomophorus gambianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see maps in 
<bibRefCitation author="BERGMANS W." box="[391,569,1842,1868]" pageId="16" pageNumber="267" pagination="75 - 146" refId="ref16897" refString="BERGMANS W. 1988. - Taxonomy and biogeography of African fruit bats (Mammalia, Megachiroptera). 1. General Introduction; material and methods; results: The genus Epomophorus Bennett, 1836. Beaufortia 38: 75 - 146." type="journal article" year="1988">Bergmans [1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="BERGMANS W." box="[584,640,1842,1868]" pageId="16" pageNumber="267" pagination="89 - 153" refId="ref16941" refString="BERGMANS W. 1989. - Taxonomy and biogeography of African fruit bats (Mammalia, Megachiroptera). 2. The genera Micropterus Matschie, 1899, Epomops Gray, 1870, Hypsignathus H. Allen, 1861, Nanonycteris Matschie, 1899, and Plerotes Andersen, 1910. Beaufortia 39: 89 - 153." type="journal article" year="1989">1989</bibRefCitation>
] and 
<bibRefCitation author="GRUBB P. &amp; JONES T. S. &amp; DAVIES A. G. &amp; EDBERG E. &amp; STARIN E. D. &amp; HILL J. E." pageId="16" pageNumber="267" refId="ref18895" refString="GRUBB P., JONES T. S., DAVIES A. G., EDBERG E., STARIN E. D. &amp; HILL J. E. 1998. - Mammals of Ghana, Sierra Leone and the Gambia. The Trendrine Press, Zennor, St. Ives, Cornwall, vi + 265 p." type="book" year="1998">
Grubb 
